UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 508/GA
1 AN ACT relating to the protection of veterans' benefits.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 40 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) For the purposes of this section:
6 (a) "Compensation" means any money, thing of value, or economic benefit
7 conferred on, or received by, any person in return for services rendered, or
8 to be rendered, by himself or herself or another;
9 (b) "Person" means any natural person, corporation, trust, partnership,
10 incorporated or unincorporated association, or any other legal entity; and
11 (c) "Veterans' benefits matter" means the preparation, presentation, or
12 prosecution of any claim affecting any person who has filed or expressed an
13 intent to file a claim for any benefit, program, service, commodity, function,
14 status, or entitlement to which is determined to pertain to veterans, their
15 dependents, their survivors, or any other individual eligible for such
16 benefits under the laws and regulations administered by the United States
17 Department of Veterans Affairs or the Kentucky Department of Veterans'
18 Affairs.
19 (2) A person shall not receive any compensation for referring any individual to
20 another person to advise or assist the individual with any veterans' benefits
21 matter.
22 (3) A person shall not receive any compensation for any services rendered in
23 connection with any claim filed within the one (1) year presumptive period of
24 active duty release unless the veteran signs a waiver stating the veteran:
25 (a) Acknowledges he or she is in the presumptive period;
26 (b) Acknowledges there are free benefits claims services available during this
27 period;
Page 1 of 4
HB050810.100 - 1699 - XXXX 2/12/2026 2:44 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 508/GA
1 (c) Waives the use of the free services; and
2 (d) Agrees to pay for assistance with the veterans' benefits matter.
3 (4) A person seeking to receive compensation for advising, assisting, or consulting
4 any individual with any veterans' benefits matter shall, before rendering any
5 services, memorialize all terms regarding the individual's payment of fees for
6 services rendered in a written agreement signed by both parties that specifies:
7 (a) No initial or nonrefundable fee shall be charged; and
8 (b) Fees for representation or assistance shall not include interest and shall not
9 exceed five (5) times the one (1) month increase in benefits, not to exceed
10 twelve thousand five hundred dollars ($12,500).
11 (5) A person seeking to receive compensation for advising, assisting, or consulting
12 any individual with any veterans' benefits matter or engaging in the preparation
13 of an initial claim for a fee shall not:
14 (a) Utilize international call centers or data centers for processing any
15 veterans' personal information;
16 (b) Aggressively or directly solicit business regarding any veterans' benefit
17 matter; or
18 (c) Gain direct access to any personal medical, financial, or government
19 benefits log-in, username, or password information.
20 (6) A person seeking to receive compensation for advising, assisting, or consulting
21 any individual with any veterans' benefits matter may utilize an independent
22 medical professional for a medical exam but shall not utilize a medical
23 professional with whom the person has an employment or business relationship.
24 (7) A person shall not advertise or guarantee, either directly or by implication, that
25 any individual is certain to receive specific veterans' benefits or that any
26 individual is certain to receive a specific level, percentage, or amount of veterans'
27 benefits.
