UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 508/GA
1 (8) (a) A person shall not advise, assist, or consult for compensation any individual
2 concerning any veterans' benefits matter without clearly providing at the
3 outset of the business relationship the following disclosure both orally and
4 in writing:
5 "This business is not sponsored by, or affiliated with, the United States
6 Department of Veterans Affairs or the Kentucky Department of Veterans'
7 Affairs, or any other federally chartered veterans' service organization.
8 Other organizations, including but not limited to the Kentucky Department
9 of Veterans' Affairs, a local veterans' service organization, and other
10 federally chartered veterans' service organizations, may be able to provide
11 you with this service free of charge. Products or services offered by this
12 business are not necessarily endorsed by any of these organizations. You
13 may qualify for other veterans' benefits beyond the benefits for which you
14 are receiving services here."
15 (b) The written disclosure in paragraph (a) of this subsection shall appear in at
16 least twelve (12) point font and shall appear in a readily noticeable and
17 identifiable place in the person's agreement with the individual seeking
18 services. The individual shall verbally acknowledge understanding of the
19 oral disclosure and sign the document in which the written disclosure
20 appears to represent understanding of these provisions. The person offering
21 services shall retain a copy of the written disclosure while providing
22 veterans' benefits services for compensation to the individual and for at
23 least one (1) year after the date on which the service relations terminate.
24 (9) A person that receives compensation for advising, assisting, or consulting any
25 individual with any veterans' benefits matter for the individual's initial disability
26 claims shall report annually by December 1 to the Kentucky Department of
27 Veterans' Affairs identifying information of the person to include the:
Page 3 of 4
HB050810.100 - 1699 - XXXX 2/12/2026 2:44 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 508/GA
1 (a) Name or names under which the person conducts business; and
2 (b) Address of principal place of business and address of any office maintained
3 in Kentucky;
4 (10) A person that receives compensation for advising, assisting, or consulting any
5 individual with any veterans' benefits matter for the individual's initial disability
6 claims shall, within one hundred twenty (120) days of the request by Kentucky
7 Department of Veterans' Affairs, submit a report for the reporting year, with the
8 following information:
9 (a) Aggregate number of veterans served in Kentucky;
10 (b) Number of veterans' benefits claims approved, denied, and pending;
11 (c) Average claim return time; and
12 (d) Number of veterans who received a successful increase who have a
13 previously-assigned agent of record in a veterans' benefits matter.
14 Data provided shall exclude any items of personal financial, medical, or other
15 data deemed confidential, business privileged, or HIPPA-protected information.
16 (11) The Kentucky Department of Veterans' Affairs may, by administrative regulation
17 promulgated in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A, create and display on its
18 website a form to assist persons in providing the information required in
19 subsections (9) and (10) of this section.
20 (12) A violation of any provision of this section shall constitute an unfair, false,
21 misleading, or deceptive act or practice in the conduct of trade or commerce
22 under KRS 367.170.
23 (13) Notwithstanding this section, an attorney or law firm seeking to receive
24 compensation for advising, assisting, or consulting any individual with any
25 veterans' benefits matter shall be governed by the limitations set forth in 38
26 C.F.R. sec. 14.636.
